5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 694, L.D. 1792, “An Act Regarding the
10 Energy Policy of the State”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act to Ensure Fair and Equitable Recovery of Post-restructuring Stranded Costs'
13 Amend the bill by inserting after the title and before the enacting clause the following:
14 'Emergency preamble. Whereas, acts and resolves of the Legislature do not
15 become effective until 90 days after adjournment unless enacted as emergencies; and
16 Whereas, electricity costs are negatively impacting many Maine electricity
17 consumers; and
18 Whereas, the costs associated with the State's net energy billing programs are having
19 a disproportionate impact on businesses in the State that are vital to economic growth; and
20 Whereas, the rate design adopted by the Public Utilities Commission by order dated
21 April 30, 2025 will not provide sufficient relief for Maine's large and industrial customers;
22 and
23 Whereas, it is the policy of the State that the commission advance through its
24 decisions and orders beneficial electrification in order to achieve the emission reduction
25 and renewable energy goals of the State, reduce energy costs to consumers and provide
26 economic and climate benefits for all ratepayers pursuant to the Beneficial Electrification
27 Policy Act, enacted June 26, 2023; and
28 Whereas, in the judgment of the Legislature, these facts create an emergency within
29 the meaning of the Constitution of Maine and require the following legislation as
30 immediately necessary for the preservation of the public peace, health and safety; now,
31 therefore,'
32 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
33 following:
